On April 28, 2017, Vice President Mike Pence administered the oath of office to Alexander Acosta, the 27th Secretary of Labor for the United States. Pence reflected on President Donald Trump's first 100 days in office, highlighting the progress that has been made in terms of job creation, economic growth, and restoring America's standing in the world. Pence also praised Acosta's qualifications and expressed confidence in his ability to lead the Department of Labor and continue to prioritize job growth and opportunity for all Americans. Acosta, the son of Cuban refugees, expressed gratitude for the opportunity to serve and outlined his commitment to addressing the skills gap and supporting American workers in finding good, safe jobs.